# Model Weights

The trained model (~600MB) is hosted externally due to GitHub's file size limits.

## Quick Download

```bash
# From Hugging Face (recommended)
python scripts/download_weights.py

# From Google Drive (backup)
python scripts/download_weights.py --source gdrive
```

## Manual Download

### Option 1: Hugging Face Hub
```bash
pip install huggingface_hub
huggingface-cli download bhriguuu/hateful-meme-detection best_model.pth --local-dir ./models
```

### Option 2: Google Drive
```bash
pip install gdown
gdown https://drive.google.com/uc?id=1as0sRqAlqCbxybC1cl7QQ-JOzbm4byvl -O best_model.pth
```

### Option 3: Direct Links
- [Hugging Face](https://huggingface.co/bhriguuu/hateful-meme-detection)
- [Google Drive](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1as0sRqAlqCbxybC1cl7QQ-JOzbm4byvl/view)

## Model Info

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| Filename | `best_model.pth` |
| Size | ~600 MB |
| Format | PyTorch state dict |
| Architecture | CLIP ViT-B/32 + Cross-Attention |
| Accuracy | 61.0% |
| F1 Score | 0.6372 |

## After Download

Verify the model is in place:
```bash
ls models/
# Should show: best_model.pth
```

Then run inference:
```python
from src.inference import HatefulMemePredictor

predictor = HatefulMemePredictor("models/best_model.pth")
result = predictor.predict("path/to/meme.jpg", "meme text")
```
